    "description": "# Trello API End-to-End Framework\n\nThis collection automates a full user journey within Trello, ensuring that all critical endpoints for board and card management are functioning correctly.\n\n### ðŸ“‹ Test Coverage:\n\n1. **Setup:** Create Board, List, and Card.\n    \n2. **Manipulation:** Update Card details, add Comments, and create Checklists.\n    \n3. **Validation:** Verify data persistence via `GET` requests.\n    \n4. **Teardown:** Full cleanup by deleting the Board and its contents.\n    \n\n### ðŸš€ Automation Features:\n\n- **Environment Variables:** Uses `{{boardId}}`, `{{listId}}`, and `{{cardId}}` to pass data between requests automatically.\n    \n- **Robust Assertions:** Over 30 tests per iteration covering Status Codes, JSON Schema, and Performance (< 1500ms).\n    \n- **Portability:** Ready to be executed in CI/CD environments via Newman.\n    \n\n### âš™ï¸ How to use:\n\n1. Select the **Trello - Env (Public)** environment.\n    \n2. Add your `key` and `token` to the **Current Value** (never Initial Value).\n    \n3. Run the collection using the **Collection Runner**.",
